# Brainstorming and Ideation

## Project Title
Rising Waters: A Machine Learning Approach to Flood Prediction

## Problem Statement
Floods are one of the most destructive natural disasters, causing significant damage to lives, property, agriculture, and infrastructure. Traditional flood prediction methods are often slow and less accurate. There is a need for an intelligent system that can predict flood risk early using historical weather and rainfall data.

## Proposed Solution
This project develops a Machine Learning-based Flood Prediction System that analyzes weather parameters such as temperature, humidity, cloud cover, annual rainfall, and seasonal rainfall. The trained XGBoost model predicts whether flood conditions are likely and is deployed through a Flask web application for easy user interaction.

## Expected Outcome
- Early flood prediction
- Improved disaster preparedness
- Faster decision making
- User-friendly web application
